  "description": "Charge phase pad overhaul regression net (issue: 'start ends the charge phase / roll 2d6 shaded out / d-pad controls random panels'). Start walks the WHOLE charge flow (Declare -> Roll -> Confirm Charge Moves) and is consumed while a charge is mid-resolution instead of falling through to the End-Phase confirm; the hint bar's ☰ chip always names what Start will do; D-pad ◀ ▶ step the target rows like ▲ ▼ and never dump the player into right-panel/bottom-bar focus; A toggles the first target without needing a ▲ press first and never starts a junk carry outside the move stage; LB/RB are locked while a charge is committed (the desync that left Roll 2D6 disabled); X = Snap to Contact and B = Undo Last Model in the move stage; L3 swaps the carried model. Battlewagon drives the full happy path to a completed charge; Boyz drive the carry affordances.",
